fusion with bone graft

254
00:10:08,391 --> 00:10:09,757
between L5 and S1.

255
00:10:11,094 --> 00:10:12,371
Do you need to take that?

256
00:10:14,064 --> 00:10:15,530
Nope.

257
00:10:15,599 --> 00:10:18,599
So, Derek usually does the...

258
00:10:18,785 --> 00:10:21,246
You can take the
call. It's okay. It's fine.

259
00:10:21,270 --> 00:10:22,536
I'm sorry.

260
00:10:22,605 --> 00:10:24,050
Just because Derek
and I are having

261
00:10:24,074 --> 00:10:25,484
a hard time juggling our lives,

262
00:10:25,508 --> 00:10:27,119
that doesn't mean that we
should keep you from yours.

263
00:10:27,143 --> 00:10:28,721
You know what? I
liked you a lot better

264
00:10:28,745 --> 00:10:30,389
when you were the sister-in-law
who didn't give a crap.

265
00:10:30,413 --> 00:10:33,030
Could we just go back to
that? That would be great.

266
00:10:34,267 --> 00:10:36,985
Am I qualified to
run the department?

267
00:10:37,053 --> 00:10:38,847
Yikes. You know, not my call.

268
00:10:38,871 --> 00:10:41,267
What I do know is that
for some strange reason,

269
00:10:41,291 --> 00:10:43,636
since I was a resident,
I keep getting thrown

270
00:10:43,660 --> 00:10:47,094
the riskiest, high-profile
cardiothoracic surgeries.

271
00:10:47,163 --> 00:10:48,403
I mean, why me, you know?

272
00:10:48,465 --> 00:10:49,465
Uh-huh.

273
00:10:50,867 --> 00:10:52,967
So, you did your fellowship

274
00:10:53,036 --> 00:10:55,070
in Philadelphia under
Jack Alexander?

275
00:10:55,138 --> 00:10:56,699
Do you know Dr. Alexander?

276
00:10:56,723 --> 00:10:59,824
Such a great guy.
Really, sweet as pie.

277
00:10:59,892 --> 00:11:02,861
Which is why it was
always a little embarrassing

278
00:11:02,929 --> 00:11:05,208
when our chief of surgery
would come to me for consults

279
00:11:05,232 --> 00:11:07,031
instead of Dr. Alexander.

280
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:09,850
I took it as a compliment,
but still, awkward.

281
00:11:10,553 --> 00:11:11,919
Hmm.

282
00:11:14,891 --> 00:11:16,791
Knock, knock. Who's there?

283
00:11:16,860 --> 00:11:18,100
Interrupting jellyfish.

284
00:11:18,128 --> 00:11:19,227
Interrupting...

285
00:11:19,295 --> 00:11:21,579
That's my favorite one!

286
00:11:21,631 --> 00:11:23,164
Hey, Dr. Ross.

287
00:11:23,233 --> 00:11:25,032
Kevin doesn't need
the TPN this afternoon.

288
00:11:25,101 --> 00:11:27,085
Dr. Karev said he could
do his surgery today.

289
00:11:27,153 --> 00:11:30,271
Oh, that's... But Dr. Robbins...

290
00:11:30,340 --> 00:11:34,092
Ross, let me explain short
bowel syndrome to you.

291
00:11:34,144 --> 00:11:37,156
Kevin here is missing a
big chunk of his small bowel,

292
00:11:37,180 --> 00:11:39,430
which means he needs
surgery to lengthen it.

293
00:11:39,499 --> 00:11:42,316
The sooner we operate,
the sooner he goes home.

294
00:11:42,385 --> 00:11:44,163
Sound good to you? Yeah.

295
00:11:44,187 --> 00:11:45,932
We just need to transfer
you onto my service.

296
00:11:45,956 --> 00:11:48,396
Dr. Ross will pick up
the paperwork for you.

297
00:11:52,528 --> 00:11:54,546
Hey, I should let
Dr. Robbins know.

298
00:11:54,614 --> 00:11:55,947
He's my patient.

299
00:11:56,016 --> 00:11:58,449
Or he will be, as soon as
they sign the transfer papers.

300
00:11:58,518 --> 00:11:59,734
I don't feel good about this.

301
00:11:59,803 --> 00:12:01,368
You got two choices.

302
00:12:01,437 --> 00:12:03,066
You can feel good about
it and scrub in with me,

303
00:12:03,090 --> 00:12:05,000
or you can rat me out to Robbins

304
00:12:05,024 --> 00:12:06,969
and I tell her you didn't check
placement of some kid's feeding tube

305
00:12:06,993 --> 00:12:08,887
and he nearly died from
aspiration pneumonia.

306
00:12:08,911 --> 00:12:09,944
But that's not true.

307
00:12:10,012 --> 00:12:11,673
Yeah, but I worked
with her for years.

308
00:12:11,697 --> 00:12:13,242
You went nuts and killed my dad.

309
00:12:13,266 --> 00:12:14,732
Who's she gonna believe?

310
00:12:22,209 --> 00:12:25,409
You've already been the head of
your own department for two years.

311
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:29,258
You think I look too young.

312
00:12:29,282 --> 00:12:30,827
I finished high school early.

313
00:12:30,851 --> 00:12:32,751
Also med school.

314
00:12:32,819 --> 00:12:34,579
It's pretty annoying, right?

315
00:12:35,155 --> 00:12:36,771
Yeah, it's pretty annoying.

316
00:12:36,839 --> 00:12:38,939
Excuse me. Sorry to interrupt.

317
00:12:39,008 --> 00:12:41,676
Can I borrow
Dr. Yang for a moment?

318
00:12:41,744 --> 00:12:42,776
Excuse me.

319
00:12:46,282 --> 00:12:48,549
Hope you saved
the big guns for last.

320
00:12:48,618 --> 00:12:50,618
They're all solid
candidates on paper,

321
00:12:50,687 --> 00:12:51,927
but between the humble-bragger

322
00:12:51,954 --> 00:12:53,483
and the girl who rode
in on the big wheel...

323
00:12:53,507 --> 00:12:54,989
Cristina, I need to know

324
00:12:55,058 --> 00:12:57,220
exactly what Bailey
said to you this morning.

325
00:12:57,244 --> 00:12:58,426
About?

326
00:12:58,511 --> 00:13:00,671
Her patient, the
deactivated HIV.

327
00:13:01,464 --> 00:13:02,697
Drawing a blank.

328
00:13:02,766 --> 00:13:03,915
Really?

329
00:13:03,983 --> 00:13:05,494
Well, I've been
interviewing all day.

330
00:13:05,518 --> 00:13:06,896
I'm surprised I
remember my own name.

331
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:09,637
You know what? It's
probably for the best.

332
00:13:09,706 --> 00:13:12,440
Oh, and... Go
easy on these guys.

333
00:13:12,508 --> 00:13:14,468
You know, they can't all be you.

334
00:13:17,063 --> 00:13:19,580
Dr. Avery, I haven't
held my son in months,

335
00:13:19,666 --> 00:13:21,982
and I want him to come
out, but for all we know,

336
00:13:22,051 --> 00:13:23,995
she could be making up
numbers to cover her own ass.

337
00:13:24,019 --> 00:13:26,187
Yeah, we can't
trust that it's safe.

338
00:13:26,256 --> 00:13:28,200
I mean, what if we get him
home and something happens?

339
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:30,324
You know what? I
understand your concerns.

340
00:13:30,393 --> 00:13:31,871
What I'm saying
is if the labs show...

341
