Are you a parent, Dr. Avery?

342
00:13:39,569 --> 00:13:44,622
My wife and I are expecting.

343
00:13:44,691 --> 00:13:46,969
Well, if someone
did this to you,

344
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:49,160
your child, how would you react?

345
00:13:51,681 --> 00:13:54,498
I'll go ahead and run some
new labs for you myself.

346
00:13:59,955 --> 00:14:01,517
All right, that might
be enough weight.

347
00:14:01,541 --> 00:14:02,985
All right. Ready for that X-ray?

348
00:14:03,009 --> 00:14:04,086
Right away. Whoops!

349
00:14:04,110 --> 00:14:05,721
Looks like I need
more irrigation.

350
00:14:05,745 --> 00:14:07,145
Uh, Wilson, can you take over?

351
00:14:07,196 --> 00:14:08,546
Yes, absolutely, Dr. Kepner.

352
00:14:12,051 --> 00:14:14,052
"Absolutely, Dr. Kepner."

353
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:16,415
Who are you? I
thought you had grit.

354
00:14:16,439 --> 00:14:18,739
I do! I do have grit!

355
00:14:18,808 --> 00:14:21,087
Okay, well, all I see is some
"yes, ma'am, no ma'am" sissy girl,

356
00:14:21,111 --> 00:14:22,721
and there's no place
in ortho for sissy girls.

357
00:14:22,745 --> 00:14:24,678
Do you hear me?

358
00:14:24,747 --> 00:14:27,147
Check yourself before
you wreck yourself.

359
00:14:28,334 --> 00:14:29,784
Sweetie, look.

360
00:14:29,853 --> 00:14:32,587
This says yoga might
help. You love yoga.

361
00:14:32,655 --> 00:14:35,989
Are you crazy? I can't
do downward dog.

362
00:14:36,576 --> 00:14:37,925
In a hot room?

363
00:14:42,298 --> 00:14:45,533
A bunch of yoga won't
get me my job back.

364
00:14:45,602 --> 00:14:48,202
You lost your job over this?

365
00:14:48,271 --> 00:14:51,305
They can't fire you over
something you can't control.

366
00:14:51,374 --> 00:14:52,606
After the cancer,

367
00:14:52,676 --> 00:14:55,810
I was supposed to have
my big return to the stage.

368
00:14:55,879 --> 00:14:57,456
I was able to make
it through rehearsals,

369
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:59,880
running back and
forth to the bathroom,

370
00:14:59,949 --> 00:15:02,333
but then, the first
full run-through,

371
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:03,667
no breaks...

372
00:15:04,321 --> 00:15:05,520
Oh, no.

373
00:15:05,588 --> 00:15:08,606
Blastoff, in the
middle of a pirouette.

374
00:15:08,675 --> 00:15:10,635
The fact that it didn't
happen in front of an audience

375
00:15:10,659 --> 00:15:14,278
is the only thing that kept me
from shooting myself in the face.

376
00:15:14,347 --> 00:15:16,030
She's exaggerating.

377
00:15:16,098 --> 00:15:19,217
Paul, it was like
frickin' spin art.

378
00:15:27,294 --> 00:15:28,334
Hey, where's Kevin Platt?

379
00:15:28,395 --> 00:15:30,439
Dr. Karev took
him up to surgery.

380
00:15:30,463 --> 00:15:32,308
Hey, what, are you
poaching patients now?

381
00:15:32,332 --> 00:15:33,476
I didn't poach anything.

382
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:34,677
You stole my short gut kid.

383
00:15:34,701 --> 00:15:36,245
All right. Up until
a few weeks ago,

384
00:15:36,269 --> 00:15:37,601
he was our short gut kid.

385
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:39,903
Look, his parents know
me. They're fine with this.

386
00:15:39,972 --> 00:15:43,090
Consents are signed, and
he's just about prepped.

387
00:15:43,159 --> 00:15:44,319
Ross?

388
00:15:44,911 --> 00:15:45,993
Really?

389
00:15:48,047 --> 00:15:50,698
The kid's on the operating
table. What do you want me to do?

390
00:15:51,735 --> 00:15:53,967
This was a jerk-ass move, Karev,

391
00:15:54,036 --> 00:15:55,276
and you know it.

392
00:15:58,541 --> 00:15:59,840
So, no one's qualified?

393
00:15:59,909 --> 00:16:02,977
No, I mean,
they're all qualified...

394
00:16:03,046 --> 00:16:04,311
But Owen's right.

395
00:16:04,380 --> 00:16:07,582
I need to accept that none
of them are gonna be me.

396
00:16:07,650 --> 00:16:09,495
That's his plan.
What's his plan?

397
00:16:09,519 --> 00:16:11,836
Owen. Didn't make sense before.

398
00:16:11,904 --> 00:16:14,154
A fellow interviewing
potential department heads,

399
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:16,223
showing you a bunch
of people you won't like

400
00:16:16,292 --> 00:16:18,575
to get you to stay. He
wants to offer you the job.

401
00:16:18,644 --> 00:16:21,078
Mer, you're thinking
about this way too hard.

402
00:16:21,147 --> 00:16:22,880
You don't offer a
first-year attending

403
00:16:22,949 --> 00:16:25,049
head of cardiothoracic
surgery. It's just not done.

404
00:16:25,118 --> 00:16:27,885
You just got hired to run
an entire research facility.

405
00:16:27,954 --> 00:16:29,454
You're perfect for the job.

406
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:32,523
Wait, two seconds ago,

407
00:16:32,591 --> 00:16:34,992
I wasn't qualified to
interview the candidates,

408
00:16:35,061 --> 00:16:37,161
and now you're saying
that I'm perfect for the job?

409
00:16:37,230 --> 00:16:38,496
Yeah, because you're you.

410
00:16:38,565 --> 00:16:40,365
Okay, I'm lost.

411
00:16:40,433 --> 00:16:43,884
Is Owen the one plotting
to keep me here, or are you?

412
00:16:43,953 --> 00:16:46,186
Now you're the one
thinking about it too hard.

413
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:48,133
She's a dancer.
This isn't just a job.

414
00:16:48,157 --> 00:16:49,590
This is who she is.

415
00:16:49,659 --> 00:16:51,169
And we're just
gonna send her home

416
00:16:51,193 --> 00:16:52,605
farting and pooping
uncontrollably

417
00:16:52,629 --> 00:16:54,829
for the rest of her life? And
we're done with the chili.

418
00:16:56,516 --> 00:16:57,982
Webber told you
to take an antacid.

419
00:16:58,050 --> 00:17:00,062
I did. I drank half a bottle,
and it didn't do anything,

420
00:17:00,086 --> 00:17:01,831
and then I got all
anxious about that,

421
00:17:01,855 --> 00:17:03,466
and the next thing you know,
I'm on the train to pizza town.

422
00:17:03,490 --> 00:17:06,501
You know what you need? A
magnetic esophageal sphincter.

423
00:17:06,525 --> 00:17:08,337
Bailey put one in
an old lady last week.

424
00:17:08,361 --> 00:17:09,877
A ring of little magnets

425
00:17:09,946 --> 00:17:11,673
at the end of the esophagus,
just above the stomach.

426
00:17:11,697 --> 00:17:14,131
Lets food in, stays
closed so you don't keep...

427
00:17:15,535 --> 00:17:16,712
Doing that. Yes. Yes.

428
00:17:16,736 --> 00:17:18,119
Please get that thing.

429
00:17:18,187 --> 00:17:20,470
It's a magnetic sphincter? Yeah.

430
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:22,840
So, if it closes the opening
for the food on the way in,

431
00:17:23,877 --> 00:17:25,387
wouldn't it work on the way out?

432
00:17:25,411 --> 00:17:27,778
What, for our cancer dancer?

433
00:17:27,846 --> 00:17:31,286
It's actually pretty good. Yeah.
You should pitch it to Webber.

434
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:34,152
Hey, Edwards, you've been
working with Bailey, right?

435
00:17:34,220 --> 00:17:35,698
She was supposed
to meet me for lunch,

436
00:17:35,722 --> 00:17:37,922
but she hasn't returned any
of my calls. Something up?

437
00:17:41,561 --> 00:17:44,040
What the hell's the matter with
you? How could you be so reckless?

438
00:17:44,064 --> 00:17:45,941
How did you... I had
to hear it from Edwards!

439
00:17:45,965 --> 00:17:47,376
I sure as hell didn't
hear it from you!

440
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:48,732
I couldn't tell you.

441
00:17:48,801 --> 00:17:51,202
I didn't want you
to have to lie for me.

442
00:17:51,271 --> 00:17:54,421
Dr. Warren, I'd appreciate
it if you stepped outside.

443
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:56,289
Look, she is my wife.

444
00:18:00,112 --> 00:18:01,912
Okay, um...

445
00:18:01,981 --> 00:18:03,992
The lawyers are meeting now.

446
00:18:04,016 --> 00:18:05,861
We're discharging Braden soon,

447
00:18:05,885 --> 00:18:08,630
but it does not look like the
Morrises are going to let this go.

448
00:18:08,654 --> 00:18:10,134
So it looks like a
malpractice suit?

449
00:18:10,189 --> 00:18:11,429
Worse.

450
00:18:12,325 --> 00:18:14,275
Assault and battery charges.

451
00:18:23,052 --> 00:18:26,053
Tuck's soccer practice
is gonna be over soon.

452
00:18:26,121 --> 00:18:28,155
I was supposed to
pick him up. Can you?

453
00:18:31,093 --> 00:18:35,012
There's nothing you
can do for me here.

454
00:18:55,518 --> 00:18:56,967
Braden's coming
out of the bubble?

455
00:18:58,070 --> 00:18:59,203
Yeah.

456
00:19:03,375 --> 00:19:04,775
I wish I could have seen that.

457
00:19:08,781 --> 00:19:10,080
Suction, please.

458
00:19:12,752 --> 00:19:14,713
You can go, Ross.
I've got it from here.

459
00:19:14,737 --> 00:19:16,704
Come on. We're in the
middle of a surgery here.

460
00:19:16,773 --> 00:19:19,923
I know. You stole my patient,
but you can't steal Ross.

461
00:19:19,992 --> 00:19:22,037
He works for us.
He's my resource,

462
00:19:22,061 --> 00:19:24,578
and I need him in the NICU
doing what he was told to do.

463
00:19:25,881 --> 00:19:28,201
You need an assist?
You've got one.

464
00:19:30,586 --> 00:19:32,946
How can I be of help to you?

465
00:19:34,357 --> 00:19:36,424
Sorry, I'm having
a little bit of trouble

466
00:19:36,492 --> 00:19:38,225
dividing these
branching vessels.

467
00:19:38,294 --> 00:19:41,173
I can retract the iliac vein
medially to help with exposure.

468
00:19:41,197 --> 00:19:42,229
Thanks.

469
00:19:42,298 --> 00:19:44,543
Derek's coming
home tonight. Yup.

470
00:19:44,567 --> 00:19:46,000
Which means you can go home.

471
00:19:47,387 --> 00:19:48,497
I understand.

472
00:19:48,521 --> 00:19:50,687
I'm sorry.

473
00:19:50,756 --> 00:19:53,351
You were just trying to be
nice, and I bit your head off.

474
00:19:53,375 --> 00:19:57,144
I will be out of your
hair first thing tomorrow.

475
00:19:57,213 --> 00:19:59,479
Oh, that? No. This
is not about that.

476
00:19:59,548 --> 00:20:01,849
I've already forgotten
you said that.

477
00:20:01,918 --> 00:20:05,385
So, this isn't you kicking
me out for being a bitch?

478
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:08,222
No. No, we love having you here,

479
00:20:08,291 --> 00:20:10,257
but we don't want to
keep you from your life

480
00:20:10,326 --> 00:20:12,793
any more than we have to, so...

481
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:19,133
What's so funny?

482
00:20:19,202 --> 00:20:21,302
I'm sorry. It's just...

483
00:20:21,370 --> 00:20:24,004
If I had spoken to anyone
at Seaside Wellness

484
00:20:24,073 --> 00:20:25,818
the way I spoke to you,
I would have to have

485
00:20:25,842 --> 00:20:28,526
a conversation for
six hours about it.

486
00:20:28,594 --> 00:20:29,927
I love it here.

487
00:20:29,995 --> 00:20:32,107
James and I have
not been fighting

488
00:20:32,131 --> 00:20:33,576
about the fact
that I'm still here.

489
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:36,567
We have been fighting about
the fact that I never want to leave.

490
00:20:37,903 --> 00:20:41,988
So, you want to give
me a bionic butthole?

491
00:20:42,057 --> 00:20:43,457
It's magnetic.

492
00:20:43,526 --> 00:20:45,759
Yeah, it was Dr. Murphy's idea.

493
00:20:45,828 --> 00:20:48,762
Well, it's commonly used
as the esophageal sphincter

494
00:20:48,831 --> 00:20:50,831
to reduce reflux
and prevent food

495
00:20:50,899 --> 00:20:52,143
from coming back up the throat,

496
00:20:52,167 --> 00:20:54,468
but we think, with
a bit of modification,

497
00:20:54,537 --> 00:20:57,387
that it might work just
as well for your stool.

498
00:20:57,456 --> 00:20:58,968
Have you done this before?

499
00:20:58,992 --> 00:21:01,525
No, but it wouldn't
be the first time

500
00:21:01,594 --> 00:21:03,094
a medical device was adapted

501
00:21:03,162 --> 00:21:06,296
to something other
than its original intention.

502
00:21:06,365 --> 00:21:09,116
